I just made this recipe last night for a romantic valentine's dinner. We loved it! (Thank God we both did--as we still reek of Garlic). Like other reviewers, I made extra sauce so there was plenty to pour over the hens and potatoes. The supermarket only has frozen hens, but it didn't make the slightest difference--they were incredibly tender and moist. Just defrost for a couple of hours in luke warm water and you're set. This would definitely make a low stress dinner party recipe, as there aren't too many fiddly step.

