The roasted hens with the garlic make for a light , delicate blending of garlic flovors, tempered with just a little citrus. I serverd the hens, 1/2 each over wild rice and topped them with the sauce. My wife was very happy with the dinner. Needless to say when she's happy with the dinner I prepared for her, I'm happy.

Rating: 4
I found this to be a great easy recipe. Made it for a dinner party and got rave reviews. I did alter recipe slightly based on previous reviews. To avoid a greasy sauce, omit the 2 tbsp oil and baste w/ just broth and wine. Try cream sherry, it adds nice taste and great color. Skim pan juices with a turkey baster and thicken slightly with a roux to make a nice gravy to pass with the hens.

